  "body": "Discord link: https://discord.com/channels/629004402170134531/629004402170134537/1050744440412700682\r\nDiscord user: KuDeTa#0243\r\nDescription from the user:\r\n\r\nAt least at the merge (the last time i upgraded) the following docker-compose config worked:\r\n\r\nvolumes:\r\n `   - /home/ethereum/secrets:/secrets`\r\nwith flag:\r\n`--JsonRpc.JwtSecretFile=/secrets/jwt`\r\n\r\nI know this is still being mounted successfully because i can exec in and cat the /secrets/jwt file, which is as it should be\r\nBut, nethermind ignores this and does:\r\n```\r\n2022-12-09 08:58:11.6873|Generating authentication secret.\r\n2022-12-09 08:58:11.6873|Authentication secret has been written to file '/nethermind/keystore/jwt-secret'.\r\n2022-12-09 09:33:51.5675|Reading authentication secret from file '/nethermind/keystore/jwt-secret'\r\n```\r\n If instead i mount my jwt directly to where Nethermind expects to find it:\r\nvolumes:\r\n`- /home/ethereum/secrets/jwt:/nethermind/keystore/jwt-secret`\r\n\r\nAnd remove:\r\n `--JsonRpc.JwtSecretFile`\r\n\r\nEverything is fine",
